author: @Moontess
text:
A huge confession: I have been sleeping on aespa for a while...  But I'm totally impressed by them now.  

Let me explain: When I first started noticing them (around their debut), even I could see that they were a cut above the rest of the new girl groups.  But I was always a bit uncomfortable watching them, and I realised it was because it was quite rare that all 4 girls would look comfortable on stage.  One would always shine more while others would be placed in the background, perhaps because they were not as confident.  They were doing all these strong concepts, but I just felt like they didn't have the confidence to back it up (especially some of 'weaker' members).  It was uncomfortable for me to watch - I think I like groups that are well-rounded, where every member is able to shine in their own way and completely own their concepts.  Fast forward a few years, I am impressed with how much each member has improved.  They now all equally shine and there is a confidence in their performance that I didn't see in their earlier years.  I will definitely stan them now.
